The paper deals with a mathematical model for wireless networks, specifically the Signal-to-Interference and Noise Ratio (SINR) graph model. It uses tools from probability theory and stochastic processes to analyze the behavior of this model, including Large Deviation Principles and Asymptotic Equipartition Properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
